examples.en: A wound was contaminated by bacteria.
Don't drink the water  it's contaminated.
Be careful not to allow bacteria to contaminate the wound.
All evils here contaminate the mind. (O. Goldsmith, The Traveller, 1764)
Make sure the white paint is not contaminated by any of the other colors.
Drinking water supplies are believed to have been contaminated.
Imperfect metals infected or contaminated with terrestrial feculence.
He claims the poster ads have 'contaminated Berlin's streets'.
Garbled spices are less likely to contaminate a recipe.
